trans-unit.source: The ASIN function returns the arc sine of a specified number.

seg-source.mrk: The ASIN function returns the arc sine of a specified number.

target.mrk: The ASIN function returns the arc sine of a specified number.

trans-unit.source: The specified number is the sine, in radians, of the angle that you want. The specified number must be a <xref href="rrefsqljdoubleprecision.dita#rrefsqljdoubleprecision">DOUBLE PRECISION</xref> number.

seg-source.mrk: The specified number is the sine, in radians, of the angle that you want.
The specified number must be a <xref href="rrefsqljdoubleprecision.dita#rrefsqljdoubleprecision">DOUBLE PRECISION</xref> number.

target.mrk: The specified number is the sine, in radians, of the angle that you want.
The specified number must be a <xref href="rrefsqljdoubleprecision.dita#rrefsqljdoubleprecision">DOUBLE PRECISION</xref> number.

trans-unit.source: If the specified number is NULL, the result of this function is NULL.

seg-source.mrk: If the specified number is NULL, the result of this function is NULL.

target.mrk: If the specified number is NULL, the result of this function is NULL.

trans-unit.source: If the specified number is zero (0), the result of this function is zero.

seg-source.mrk: If the specified number is zero (0), the result of this function is zero.

target.mrk: If the specified number is zero (0), the result of this function is zero.

trans-unit.source: If the absolute value of the specified number is greater than 1, an exception is returned that indicates that the value is out of range (SQL state 22003).

target.mrk: If the absolute value of the specified number is greater than 1, an exception is returned that indicates that the value is out of range (SQL state 22003).

trans-unit.source: The returned value, in radians, is in the range -<term>pi</term>/2 to <term>pi</term>/2. The data type of the returned value is a DOUBLE PRECISION number.
